'''Guéré''' (Gere), also called '''Wè''' (Wee), is a [[Kru languages|Kru language]] spoken by over 300,000 people in the [[Dix-Huit Montagnes]] and [[Moyen-Cavally]] regions of [[Ivory Coast]].

==Phonology==
The [[phonology]] of Guere (here the Zagna dialect of Central Guere / Southern Wè)<ref>{{cite book|last=Paradis|first=Carole|year=1983|title=Description phonologique du guéré|location=Abidjan|publisher=Institut de Linguistique Appliquée, Université d'Abidjan}}</ref> is briefly sketched out below.

