Allophones of some of these phonemes include:
* {{IPA|[k͡m]}} is an allophone of {{IPA|/k͡p/}} before nasal vowels
* {{IPA|[ŋ͡m]}} is an allophone of {{IPA|/ɡ͡b/}} before nasal vowels
* {{IPA|[ŋʷ]}} is an allophone of {{IPA|/w/}} before nasal vowels
* {{IPA|[ɗ]}} is an allophone of {{IPA|/l/}} in word-initial position
* {{IPA|[r]}} is an allophone of {{IPA|/l/}} after a [[coronal consonant]] (alveolar or palatal)
In addition, while the nasal consonants {{IPA|/m, n/}} and contrast with {{IPA|/ɓ/}} and {{IPA|/l/}} before oral vowels, and are thus separate phonemes, before nasal vowels only the nasal consonants occur. {{IPA|/ɓ/}} and {{IPA|/l/}} do not occur before nasal vowels, suggesting that historically a [[Phonemic differentiation|phonemic merger]] between these sounds and the nasals {{IPA|/m, n/}} may have occurred in this position.

===Vowels===
Like many [[West Africa]]n languages, Guere makes use of a contrast between [[vowel]]s with [[advanced tongue root]] and those with [[retracted tongue root]]. In addition, [[nasal vowel]]s contrast phonemically with [[oral vowel]]s.

