The '''Mangayat''' (also, '''Bugwa''' and '''Bukwa''') are an ethnic group living in the [[South Sudan]]ese state of [[Western Bahr el Ghazal]].<ref>[http://www.gurtong.org/resourcecenter/people/profile_tribe.asp?TribeID=100 Gurtong Peace Project]</ref> 

They speak [[Mangayat]], a [[Niger–Congo language]]. The number of persons in this ethnic group likely is below 1000.<ref>http://starling.rinet.ru/typology.pdf</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ecoi.net/190169::sudan/328801.325362.9479...lk/languages.htm|title=Sudan |publisher=European Country of Origin Information Network|website=ecoi.net}}</ref>

